Eskom and the Special Investigating Unit is briefing the media today about corruption within the power utility. It's expected to make an important announcement. Ministers Pravin Gordhan and Ronald Lamola will also form part of the briefing. Editor's note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom and the Special Investigating Unit will give an update on investigations into corruption at the utility on Friday. Public Enterprises Minister, Pravin Gordhan, and Justice Minister, Ronald Lamola, are expected to attend the briefing. An important announcement is expected.